        "label": "Google Cloud OAuth 2.0 access token",
        "generateUrl": "https://console.cloud.google.com/apis/credentials",
        "setup": "Create Google Cloud credentials for your environment, then mint an access token using Google Cloud auth. The easiest local path is to [install the gcloud CLI](https://docs.cloud.google.com/sdk/docs/install-sdk) and run [`gcloud auth application-default login`](https://docs.cloud.google.com/docs/authentication/set-up-adc-local-dev-environment) or [`gcloud auth login`](https://docs.cloud.google.com/sdk/docs/authenticate), then use the resulting OAuth 2.0 access token in REST calls. For production/server use, Google Cloud docs direct you to use [Application Default Credentials](https://docs.cloud.google.com/docs/authentication/provide-credentials-adc) or a service account attached to the runtime. If you need to register your own OAuth client, use [APIs & Services → Credentials](https://console.cloud.google.com/apis/credentials).",
        "acquisition": "manual"
